## 4. Project Structure

- Use the Symfony binary to generate projects.
- Follow the default directory structure:
  - Place code in `src/` organized **by type**, not by feature or bundle.
  - Use PascalCase for folders and class names.

### Example Folders:

| Type       | Description                                                  | Folder             |
|------------|--------------------------------------------------------------|--------------------|
| Controller | Handles HTTP request/response                                | `Controller/`      |
| Entity     | Domain object, Doctrine-mapped                               | `Entity/`          |
| Repository | Query logic for entities                                     | `Repository/`      |
| Service    | Stateless domain or technical logic                          | `Service/`         |
| DTO        | Data Transfer Object, no business logic                      | `Dto/`             |
| FormType   | Symfony Form definitions                                     | `Form/Type/`       |
| Event      | Domain or system events                                      | `Event/`           |
| Listener   | Responds to a specific event                                 | `EventListener/`   |
| Subscriber | Subscribes to multiple events                                | `EventSubscriber/` |
| Voter      | Access control decisions                                     | `Security/Voter/`  |
| Command    | CLI commands (Symfony Console)                               | `Command/`         |
| Twig       | Custom Twig filters/functions                                | `Twig/Extension/`  |
| Handler    | Manages use-case-oriented processes                          | `Handler/`         |
| Manager    | Encapsulates business logic per entity                       | `Manager/`         |
| Provider   | Supplies external or internal data                           | `Provider/`        |
| Decorator  | Adds responsibilities dynamically to services                | `Decorator/`       |
| Bridge     | Integrates third-party SDKs or APIs                          | `Bridge/`          |
| Factory    | Creates configured complex objects                           | `Factory/`         |
| Normalizer | Transforms entities for serialization                        | `Normalizer/`      |
| Transformer| Converts internal data formats                               | `Transformer/`     |
| Mailer     | Email creation and dispatching                               | `Mail/`            |
| PDF        | PDF generation from templates                                | `PDF/`             |
| Excel      | Excel file export/import                                     | `Excel/`           |
| Constraint | Custom Symfony validation rules                              | `Validator/Constraint/` |
| Facade     | Simplified API over complex subsystems                       | `Facade/`          |
| Helper     | Utility classes (static or injectable)                       | `Helper/`          |
| Security   | Auth providers, firewalls, roles, etc.                       | `Security/`        |
